  <description type="morphology">Stem rounded-pentagonal in section. Leaves flattened, lanceolate, distal margins
        plane, entire or weakly toothed, not bordered; apex acute, plane or keeled; basal cells
        differentiated across leaf base as a U or V, commonly running up margins, not distinctly
        enlarged submarginally; distal laminal cells pluripapillose with low papillae; mucro conic,
        of 3–6 cells. Sexual condition dioicous. Peristome teeth bluntly lanceolate.</description>
  <description type="morphology">widely distributed in temperate and high-elevation tropical areas of the
        world</description>
  <description type="morphology">ranging into the Arctic.</description>
